The paper discusses training policies for continuous control tasks using simple linear and RBF parameterizations, which are common techniques in machine learning and optimization. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with control tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to Robotics (cs.RO) or Systems and Control (cs.SY). The use of policies to solve tasks also suggests that it could belong to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the OpenAI gym benchmarks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks, suggesting that it could also belong to Computer Vision (cs.CV).
